result.name: Bloop Shisha Lounge

reviews.text:
Drinks are quite expensive and the Shisha as well. But the Shisha is great, they are using the right tobacco and the right charcoal. 
The view from the balcony is nice. 
Be careful not to let yourself be dragged to the third floor.  There is also a shisha lounge but not comparable to Bloop and they intercept customers who go to the Bloop on the 21st floor

Been there half a year ago. It was the best bar I've ever been:) the drinks, food, environment, and the service were all 💯. But be aware of the price cuz its pretty expensive. 
Drinks were average 100HKD and fries were around 100HKD but are really 🔥
Shisha was good, but a bit light. Fries were great. Drinks were good
A bit crowded but the service was wonderful. Thank you Danny!
Great place for shisha

result.name: Charcoal HK

reviews.text: The place is very dark, I went there on a rainy day with 3 friends.  Since it stopped raining by the time we arrived, I didn't notice that all the chairs were wet so I sat on it and my short was all wet, it's quite uncomfortable to sit there all night wearing a wet short.  The staff didn't apologise for not putting up those chairs or warn us that those are wet.  Other than that, the service was good, the server recommended an exclusive drink and shisha flavour, which was quite nice.  I enjoyed it despite the incident.
Service is just bad. place very expensive and not worth it. Would not recommend
the worst Shisha bar in Hong Kong. Expensive and definitely not worth it. Bad service attitude.
Great environment and customer service - Barry and team are the absolute nicest!! Definitely my favourite shisha bar in HK :)
The sisha was avarage.I smoke for 15 years. Had to ask to change coal. they charge straight away for the glass one-not even asking. 350 hkd. the view from the terrace not worth. wwould not go again.
